.TH RUSHX 1 "February 2026" "RushX 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rushx \- POSIX-style shell and terminal emulator (early prototype)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rushx
[\fB--rushx-shell\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
RushX is a Rust-based terminal emulator and shell. By default it launches the
terminal emulator window. With \fB--rushx-shell\fR it runs an interactive shell
REPL in the terminal.

The current shell implementation is minimal and supports only a small set of
built-in commands.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --rushx-shell
Start the interactive shell REPL instead of the GUI terminal.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B echo \fIARGS...\fR
Print arguments to stdout.
.TP
.B type \fICOMMAND\fR
Report whether COMMAND is a shell builtin or an executable found in PATH.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.rushxrc
Planned configuration file (not yet implemented).
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns 0 on normal exit. Unrecognized commands print an error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Launch the GUI terminal:
.B rushx
.TP
Run the shell REPL:
.B rushx --rushx-shell
.TP
Find a command:
.B type ls
